title: Los Freddy's Aquel Amor LP (vinyl rip)
description:
This is very old vinyl rip of Los Freddy&#039;s 
"Aquel Amor" LP from 1975. This LP is 
long OUT-OF-PRINT and was on of my 1st 
attempts at ripping vinyl in 1997.

Quality isn&#039;t great, my family must have 
played this LP nearly 10,000 times before
1980 (!), but it&#039;s now available to any one 
who is interested, or fondly remembers early 
early 70&#039;s Mexican Romantica music.

By 1975, FREDDY&#039;S (as Los Freddy&#039;s were calling 
themselves then), had all but abandoned their 
garage rock n roll roots and were in the midst of 
spearheading an new type of Mexican music called 
ROMANTICA. 

Enjoy!!

Also available are the following out-of-print
Los Freddy&#039;s LP&#039;s:

Mato Mi Corazon (1967?)
Obsesion (1968?)
Sin Tu Amor (1969?)
Lagrimas Son (1970?)
Con Tu Adios (1972)
Quiero Ser Feliz (1973)
Llegara Tu Final (1974)
Aquel Amor (1975)

If you want them...ask.
